  "description": "This dataset comprises concurrent electrical stimulation and functional MRI (es-fMRI) recordings from 26 patients with medically refractory epilepsy who had surgically implanted intracranial electrodes. The resource includes BOLD-fMRI responses to electrical stimulation of cortical and subcortical sites, along with anatomical imaging, resting-state scans, field maps, and electrode localization data. Pre-processed derivatives using fMRIprep and FreeSurfer are provided, enabling investigation of brain network responses to direct electrical stimulation.",
  "methods_description": "Electrical stimulation was delivered through implanted intracranial electrodes during functional MRI acquisition using a block design. Data were collected in two sessions: pre-operative (baseline imaging) and post-operative (es-fMRI with stimulation). Anatomical imaging included T1-weighted and T2-weighted sequences. Stimulation parameters and electrode coordinates are documented for each run.",
